<subSubSection id="CFE3650DB03B8805FF42FD3B980477E6" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="87463686B03B8805FF42FD3B9E4C7706" blockId="5.[174,1232,655,970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Hosts: European mouflon (P = 20 %; I = 17.5 (1–34)); common eland (P = 21.1 %; I = 2.9 (1–10)); markhor (P = 9.1 %; I = 1); saiga antelope (P = 21.7 %; I =1.2 (1–4)); Barbary sheep (P = 40 %; I = 1.5 (1–2)); American bison (P = 45.5 %; I = 2.2 (1–4)); nilgai (P = 28.6 %; I = 1); red deer (P = 16.7 %; I = 1); guanaco (P = 16.7 %; I = 1).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87463686B03B8805FF42FCBB98047766" blockId="5.[174,1232,655,970]" box="[227,603,815,842]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Site of infection: small intestine.</paragraph>
